Phase 4 — Catalog management
Service: catalog-service · MongoDB `catalog` db

Purely additive on top of Phase 3's products collection — no new fields,
only new mutation endpoints against rows that already exist.

Scenarios covered: 13, 14, 15.

---

## PATCH /api/products/{id}  (admin only)

Scenario 13. CAT-010: changing price/name/description/category affects
only future orders — orders already placed keep their ORD-005 snapshot
regardless of what this endpoint does afterward.

Request:
```json
PATCH /api/products/10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for admin>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "unitPrice": "84.99"
}
```

Response — 200 OK:
```json
{
  "id": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
  "name": "Trail Runner 2.0",
  "unitPrice": "84.99",
  "stockCount": 25,
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "updatedAt": "2026-07-13T13:00:00Z"
}
```

Note for the phase after this one: an order placed before this call keeps
`unitPriceSnapshot: "89.99"` on its order_items row — verify this
explicitly once Phase 5 exists, since it's the first place CAT-010 and
ORD-005 actually interact.

