## PATCH /api/products/{id}/status  (admin only)

Scenario 14. CAT-008: an Administrator can deactivate a product; it
becomes fully hidden from browsing and unorderable regardless of stock —
distinct from CAT-007's out-of-stock-but-visible state.

Request:
```json
PATCH /api/products/10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000005/status
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for admin>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "DEACTIVATED"
}
```

Response — 200 OK:
```json
{
  "id": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000005",
  "status": "DEACTIVATED",
  "updatedAt": "2026-07-13T13:15:00Z"
}
```

After this call, GET /api/products/10000000-...-0005 (Phase 3) must
return 404, and it must be absent from GET /api/products entirely — that's
the regression check for this endpoint specifically, not just a one-time
assertion.

